\section{Numerical Results}\label{Numerical Results}
In the simulation, we set the frame period to be $T=1$ s, the transmit power of PBs to be $P_p=43$ dBm, the number of antennas of PB to be $M=32$, the carrier frequency for power transfer to be $900$ MHz, and the energy conversion efficiency of WPT to be $\eta=0.8$. In addition, it is assumed that the target probability of detection ${{\bar P}_d}$ is $90\%$. In this paper, we let $d_0\geq 1$~m to make sure the path loss of WPT is equal or greater than one.  In the following part, $\rm{SNR} = \frac{{\sigma _s^2}}{{{\sigma ^2}}}$ refers to the SNR in sensing channels.

